<br>
Maybe we're some of those clueless people or our equipment sucks, but there are still plenty of XP situations where we NEED a cleric. Even with 1090 AC, a frost giant elite requires constant greater healing from a paladin/druid. We don't always (or even usually) have an enchanter or shaman for slow. Our group has always tended to be tank heavy (2 paladins and a ranger; used to be 2 paladins and 2 rangers), and a cleric has always made things easier.<br>
<br>
I have never seen a cleric have to shout LFG more than twice. Never. Maybe that changes in the upper 50's (I'm 56 at the moment), but currently clerics always seem in demand. It is hard for me to imagine this change hurting clerics.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, I'd like to see clerics get a little boost. I would hate to play a cleric just because they really are close to one dimensional. One area I'd like to see them improved is in terms of buffs. Their AC line (and ours) kind of stinks right now. I was shocked to find that Shield of Words added only 6 more AC over my Armor of Faith. It seems like rangers buff AC better than clerics.<br>
<br>
